column9: 15. Wear the kind of clothes you like even if they are different from what others wear.
column10: 16. In a line-up, tell a student who pushes in front of you to wait his or her turn.
column11: 17. Stand up for yourself when another kid in class makes fun of you.
column12: 18. Help a student who is visiting your school for a short time to have fun and interesting experiences.
column13: 19. Join a school club or sports team.
column14: 20. Express your feelings to another kid.
column15: 21. Ask someone over to your house on a Saturday.
column16: 22. Ask someone to go to a school dance or movie with you.
column17: 23. Go to a party where you are sure you won’t know any of the kids.
column18: 24. Ask another student for help when you need it.
column19: 25. Make friends with kids your age.
column20: 1. You can learn new things, but you can’t really change your basic intelligence.
column21: 2. Your intelligence is something about you that you can’t change very much.
column22: 3. You have a certain amount of intelligence and you really can’t do much to change it.
